CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 7, 1962, pg. 5, reads: "Scranton in Hill District - Congressman William W. Scranton, gubernatorial candidate on the Republican ticket, made a whirlwind tour of the city's Hill District, Monday morning, to see at first hand and to shake hands with voters. Accompanied by his wife, Mrs. Mary Scranton, he stopped at... (2) on Centre Ave., where he shook hands with Charles C. Wilson and other citizens... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Pennsylvania gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton shaking hands with Charles C. Wilson on Centre Avenue, Hill District
